                "value": 0.0348
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Enriched isotopes of 204Pb",
                "were obtained in the form of Pb(NO3)2 crystals.",
                "Targets were prepared in the usual manner by using",
                "the lead nitrate crystals as received or in a few",
                "cases by using lead powder which was",
                "electrochemically reduced from an aqueous solution of",
                "the nitrate. The amount of lead in the prepared",
                "target usually ranged between 0.5 and 3.0 mg."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP",
                "EXTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Targets of the enriched 204Pb were",
                "bombarded with helium ions and the fission fragment",
                "cross sections determined radiochemically. The",
                "targets were then flown to our laboratories in",
                "Bellingham where the fission fragments were separated",
                "and purified by the standard radiochemical",
                "techniques. The period of time between end of",
                "bombardment and counting the purified samples was",
                "short enough (~15 hr.) and the fission cross sections",
                "high enough that even 2.7 hr 92Sr could be easily",
                "identified. Due to the expense of the target material,",
                "most of the bombardments were made using the 73",
                "percent enriched isotope (Sample #1). The value",
                "measured experimentally, however, was the total",
                "fission cross section for all the isotopes present.",
                "The value of the fission cross section for 204Pb",
                "alone was then resolved by subtracting the",
                "contributions from all the \"impurity\" isotopes."
              ]
            }
          ],
